<plot>"One In A Million" is a feature length documentary, shot mostly on 1080P/24P HD, about the filmmaker's family - and their learning curve, reality shift to, and understanding of, their daughter, Lucy, and her autism spectrum disorder, specifically Asperger's syndrome. While including some expert opinions, it is mostly about this chapter of Lucy's life, which began before her diagnosis in January 2007, and continues to this day. The title is a play on words of the autism statistic "One In 150", as in we don't believe our daughter is a statistic.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?412914</url></doc>
